modules.description: This module handles network device operations using Lwt for asynchronous I/O, providing functions to send and receive Ethernet frames, retrieve and reset interface statistics, and manage connection state. It works with buffers represented as `Cstruct.t`, MAC addresses via `Macaddr.t`, and custom result and error types for network operations. Concrete use cases include sending raw Ethernet packets, listening for incoming traffic with a callback, and monitoring or resetting network interface statistics.

This module implements network device operations using Lwt for asynchronous I/O, enabling sending and receiving of Ethernet frames, retrieval and reset of interface statistics, and management of connection state. It operates on data types such as `Cstruct.t` for buffers, `Macaddr.t` for MAC addresses, and custom result and error types for handling network operations. You can use it to send raw Ethernet packets, listen for incoming traffic with a callback function, or monitor and reset network interface statistics.
